Management Accountant
Reporting to the Financial Director of this award winning, multi-site retail group, the Management Accountant will supervise a small team and will take responsibility for the production of management accounts as well as assisting the FD on improving reporting, budgeting and cash management.

As Finance Manager, you will be responsible for overseeing all production of consolidated accounts, statutory accounts, monthly accounts preparation, bank reconciliations, VAT returns, payroll along with many ad hoc projects.

To succeed in this role you must be a qualified accountant seeking your first move from practice, be able to demonstrate the ability to communicate effectively at all levels and possess strong technical accounting skills. This is a fantastic opportunity for any individual looking to join an organisation currently going through an exciting period of growth and expansion.
